Cloud Detective Kit
Automated Cloud Digital Forensics and Incident Response Framework

Author
Kathan Majithiya
Abstract
Cloud computing environments generate a massive volume of logs that are critical for forensic investigations. Manual analysis of cloud logs is time-consuming and prone to human error. This project presents the Cloud Detective Kit, an automated cloud forensic investigation framework designed to analyze AWS CloudTrail logs, detect suspicious activities, reconstruct attack timelines, map events to the MITRE ATT&CK framework, calculate risk scores, and generate Digital Forensics and Incident Response (DFIR) reports.
The framework automates the collection, normalization, analysis, and reporting of cloud forensic evidence. Detection rules were implemented for suspicious EC2 enumeration activities, STS AssumeRole privilege escalation attempts, and S3 reconnaissance behavior. The generated reports provide investigators with actionable insights and reduce manual investigation effort.

1. Introduction
Cloud environments present unique forensic challenges due to distributed infrastructure, dynamic resources, and large-scale logging systems. Traditional forensic approaches are often insufficient for cloud-native investigations.
AWS CloudTrail provides detailed logs of user and service activities. These logs contain valuable forensic evidence that can be analyzed to identify suspicious behavior, attacker actions, and security incidents.
The Cloud Detective Kit was developed to automate cloud forensic analysis and generate investigation-ready reports.

